\begin{verbatim}
SdofFreeTimeProblem(sdof, u0, t)
\end{verbatim}
Structure containing the data of a time problem for a sdof system

\textbf{Fields}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{sdof::Sdof}: Sdof structure


\item \texttt{u0::AbstractVector}: Initial conditions

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{x0}: Initial displacement [m]


\item \texttt{v0}: Initial velocity [m/s]

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{t::AbstractRange}: Time points at which to evaluate the response

\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
solve(prob::SdofFreeTimeProblem)
\end{verbatim}
Compute the free response of a single degree of freedom (Sdof) system.

\textbf{Input}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{prob}: Structure containing the parameters of the Sdof problem

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{sol}: The response of the system at the given time points

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{u}: Displacement solution


\item \texttt{du}: Velocity solution


\item \texttt{ddu}: Acceleration solution

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

